main event: A sighting of a large, dark, saucer-shaped object that appeared to be hovering or floating in the sky over Lanham, Maryland on December 7, 1965.
interesting points: The object had no visible lights and appeared metallic in appearance, around 30-40 feet in diameter, and was moving slowly across the sky.
The witness was unable to discern any specific details or features of the object, but it did not resemble any known aircraft.
The object seemed to just float silently and then disappeared, leading the witness to refer to it as a 'spacecraft'.
The Air Force analysis concluded that the sighting could be related to a project at Northwestern University involving 'lampost vehicles', but the object remained unidentified.
The witness had never seen this or a similar object before and reported the sighting to the authorities.
